              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><b>Corto</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/07/2002&nbsp;: 2:43:50 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I hunted these guys from 47-51.  I don't really remember what I did before I hit 49 so I won't touch on that, although I can say thery were very good exp at that time as well.  This guide is for once you turn level 49 and get your new spells.<br /><br /><br /><b><u>Time - 45-50min per yellow at level 50</u></b> (Thats all of level 50 in under 4 hours!)<br /><br /><br /><b><u>Spells:</u></b><br />1. Bond of Death<br />2. Pact of Shadow<br />3. Shackle of Spirit<br />4. Venom of Snake<br />5. Augment Death<br />6. Lich<br />7. Harmsheild<br />8. Feign Death<br /><br /><br /><b><u>Location:</u></b><br />(-2800, 2800) Entrance to Emperor Ganak's Mausoleum<br /><br /><br /><b><u>Technique</u></b><br /><br /><b>Keepers</b> - Send pet, BoD target, Pact pet, sit and med.  Some Keepers will have a DS on which hurts the pet some, cast Shackle of Spirit on these to offset the melee damage.<br /><br /><b>Champions</b> - Send Pet, Shackle of Spirit target, BoD target, Pact pet, sit and med.  If you're really high on mana then cast a VoS on him to speed up the kill.<br /><br /><b>Commanders</b> - Send Pet, Shackle of Spirit target, BoD target, VoS target, Pact Pet, sit and med.  I usually ended up casting a second BoD and a second Pact for my pet.<br /><br /><br /><b><u>Important Notes!!</u></b><br />- I sat on the top of the steps at the entrance to Emperor Ganak's Mausoleum and went afk for hours with no problems, very safe spot.<br />- Spectrals DO NOT help each other.  You could have two of them right on top of each other and one will never help the other.<br />- <u>Looting is the most dangerous part of this camp!</u>  These guys pop randomly so you never know when one if going to pop right on top of you.  So stay out of range (on the steps) during fights, and be very careful when you run down to loot.<br />- I say DO NOT FEAR because they run pretty far away and it's just easier to keep them close to you.  Plus your 49 pet is strong enough that they don't need feared.<br />- If you get an add because you didn't listen to my advice above, don't panic.  FD immediately, and if your pet can't kill it then you need to /q.  These guys do not forget you ever so always use /q when you need to get rid of aggro.<br /><br /><br /><b><u>Conclusion</u></b> - Good lord why are you still reading this and haven't gone to this camp yet!  I completed level 50 in 4 hours at this place now get going!!<br /><br /><br />Insert witty comment and original artwork here.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
