                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">jebarizy</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/23/2003&nbsp;: 10:03:58 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> The spectre camp at the entrance to Emperor Ganak's mausoleum is fantastic xp and good money at levels 49 and 50.  Words to the wise:<br /><br />1.  Be VERY careful while looting.  I sucked up one death when I was jumped by a respawn running back to camp from looting.  FD isn't 100% reliable, as the spectral keepers cast and can knock you out of it.  If in doubt, leave the farthest corpses to rot - 5pp isn't worth a death.<br /><br />2.  Don't even think of casting while standing anywhere in the bowl of the spectre area.  Respawns are a real danger.  If you have to be down off the steps or the wall to cast on the mob, it's too far away.  Wait 30 seconds.  They'll make more.<br /><br />3.  Make sure you get your pet on the keepers and wait for one taunt before casting on them.  The higher level ones could cast on me at levels 49 and 50 for a max of about 300 DD.  You can win a lifetap - nuke war with them, but you don't want to start one if you're low on health from pacting your pet and liching.  Let the pet get and maintain aggro.  This is generally good advice but is especially important for the keepers as they can cast and knock you out of FD.  The champions and commanders are warrior types and do not cast, BTW.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
