                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/10/2002&nbsp;: 5:10:49 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I hunted here from lvl 48-51. Died a couple of times from my own stupidity, but once i got it going it was sweet. All you need is Darkness and invoke fear and either bond of death (49 and up) or vamp curse and drain spirit (for obvious health reasons) for the keepers. For the Champions and commanders you need to add in some dot's. It's real simple to pull one at a time too since they don't help each other out unless you get into their aggro zone. Personally I sent pet in first then hit doom and and fear (in case doom doesnt work pet takes him on), once those are up use your life taps to keep your health up while you are power medding. Usually this takes the the keepers down to about 25% no prob for your pet. and with the dot's you cast on the higher lvl ones it takes them to about 30-45%. Jes make sure that you are sitting far enough away because as soon as the fear breaks he WILL be coming for you if you are sitting NO matter where you are (good for pet for free hits). Stand Up and it will go back to your pet. Another fear and its over. Go collect your 8 silver to 6 pp. Just be on the lookout for the frogs. Eventhough the avg. frog you see is green they do attack for some reason. There are also some blue frogs out there too. I never got to all four of the camps. Only did a three camp rotation. Hope this helps you guys out.<br /><br />How would you like your bones....ah hell I'll jes burn em<br /><br /> </span></font></td>
