                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Gunkk</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/05/2002&nbsp;: 5:02:12 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><br />Is this buggy or usual, and if so, will sending in pet avoid my being zapped for over 1/4 of my hp?<br /><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote><br /><br />"Working as intended."  EDIT: I noticed that your placement affects the fear pathing.  If you sit further South than East/West of the mob, they run due South.  If you sit too far to the East of the mob, they run to the East.  I think this has to do with the direction in which you or Jabober first draws aggro.  I always sat to the South and they always came South when feared.  Sitting to the East side of the Tower (Southeastern most EJ camp) might get you out of the wandering mob pathing and result in fewer adds, but I never bothered with it.<br /><br /><br />To avoid the Keepers' nukes, first use Sense the Dead to target the nearest one, then click this hotkey:<br /><br />/pet attack<br />/pause 20 (adjust this as needed to allow pet to gain aggro)<br />/cast *Dooming*<br />/pause *casting time*  <br />/cast *fear*<br /><br />If you're sitting inside casting range, the first /pause delay of 20 should allow the pet to draw aggro and eat the nuke for you just as darknes lands.  Usually the Keepers start casting immediately after the attacking pet gets into aggro range.<br /><br /><br />re: EJ zoneline faction hits<br /><br />No hits there either... <br /><br /><br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310159" target="_blank">Gunkk</a><br />54 Iksar Necro<br />The Nameless<br /><br /><br />Edited by - Gunkk on 11/05/2002  17:07:20</span></font></td>
              </tr>
